other_tests.findings: Initial ECG showed normal sinus rhythm with a subtle J-point elevation in leads II, III, aVF, and V2 through V6. A repeat ECG evolved to marked ST elevation and a convex shape in the lateral leads, with a decrease in R-wave progression.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Progressed from normal sinus rhythm with subtle J-point elevation to marked ST elevation and decreased R-wave progression.

other_tests.findings: Demonstrated a large thrombus occupying most of the length and approximately 70% of the diameter of the left main coronary artery, with almost 90% occlusion. A second thrombus occluded the distal left anterior descending coronary artery.
Left internal mammary artery was grafted to the left anterior descending coronary artery and a saphenous vein graft to the left circumflex artery.
